title: Nease rallies in fourth quarter to beat West Nassau
text:
Nease rallies in fourth quarter to beat West Nassau 
Sat, Oct 10, 2015 @ 12:29 am 
NEASE 44 
WEST NASSAU 30 
Star of the game: Nease junior QB Leighton Alley ran for two scores and passed for another as the Panthers (4-2) rallied to beat West Nassau (4-2). Alley’s 1-yard run with 9:28 to play gave Nease the lead after it trailed by as many as 10 in the third quarter. 
Turning point: West Nassau took a 30-21 lead late in the third quarter, then recovered an onside kick. But Nease forced two fumbles in the next three minutes and scored two quick TDs — a 22-yard run by RB Kendric Harris on the first play of the fourth quarter and a 1-yarder by Alley — to regain the lead. 
On defense: Nease’s Bailey Lynch forced a Jenkins fumble on a blitz and Johnny Bogle recovered at the West Nassau 38 to set up Alley’s go-ahead score. … West Nassau’s Hunter Hutcheson picked off a pass and returned the ball 65 yards for a touchdown to give the Warriors a 21-14 halftime lead. 
Fast facts: Harris rushed for 134 yards and two TDs. … West Nassau RB Davion Dubose rushed for 99 yards, including a 65-yard TD. … Nease senior WR Reidar Hubbard had nine catches for 141 yards and a TD on an 8-yard reception. 
They said it: “The second half of tonight’s game is hopefully something we can carry over to the second half of the season.” — Nease coach Tim Krause Ward Clayton For the Times-Union
